data.value:
After the Treaty of Lausanne, the second term Assembly made the following reforms: 29 October 1923'the declaration of sovereignty, the state was determined the way of administration. On 3 March 1924, “the repeal of the caliphate and the Dynasty-I Osmaniye, memalik the Republic of Turkey-i hariciye to removing, and on the same day, Legislative foundations, and the Erkan-ı Harbiye Ministry of oneness with the abolition of the law on unification of Education Law was also adopted. All schools and madrasahs affiliated to the power of law were closed with the abolition of the power of law and the removal of the power of law. With the adoption of the Tevhid-I Tedrisat (education and training) law, the education and training works of all schools were left to the administration of the Ministry of National Education in line with the principles of national and secularism. The courts of Shariah were abolished and the courts were merged on April 8, 1924.
On 20 April 1924, the Constitution, which gave a new order to the state, was adopted by the Turkish Grand National Assembly. The excise tax was abolished on February 17, 1925. Abolishment of the Sultanate and the caliphate, unity in education, and the Republic's declaration of the new reforms introduced by adding new ones, the efforts to renew continued. On November 25, 1925, the hat law was abolished and the Fez was abolished.
